Class BTOManagementSystem

java.lang.Object
bto.Boundaries.BTOManagementSystem
public class BTOManagementSystem extends Object
Main entry point for the BTO (Build-To-Order) Management System. Manages system initialization, data loading, and saving, and coordinates interactions between various controllers.

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Main method to launch the BTO Management System. Sets up a shutdown hook to save data and initializes the system.
      Parameters:
      args - Command-line arguments (not used)

    • initialize

      public static void initialize()
      Initializes all system controllers, file manager, and loads existing data. Creates the user interface after data loading.

    • loadData

      public static void loadData()
      Loads system data from persistent storage. Initializes controllers with loaded data and performs post-loading setup.

    • printLoadingStatus

      private static void printLoadingStatus(List<Applicant> applicants, List<HDBOfficer> officers, List<HDBManager> managers, List<Project> projects, List<ProjectApplication> applications, List<Enquiry> enquiries, List<OfficerRegistration> registrations, List<Withdrawal> withdrawals, List<FlatBooking> bookings, List<Receipt> receipts)
      Prints a summary of loaded entities to the console. Provides visibility into the number of entities loaded during initialization.
      Parameters:
      applicants - List of loaded applicants
      officers - List of loaded HDB officers
      managers - List of loaded HDB managers
      projects - List of loaded projects
      applications - List of loaded project applications
      enquiries - List of loaded enquiries
      registrations - List of loaded officer registrations
      bookings - List of loaded flat bookings
      receipts - List of loaded receipts

    • postLoadSetup

      private static void postLoadSetup(List<Applicant> applicants, List<HDBOfficer> officers, List<HDBManager> managers, List<Project> projects, List<ProjectApplication> applications, List<Enquiry> enquiries, List<Withdrawal> withdrawals, List<FlatBooking> bookings, List<Receipt> receipts)
      Performs post-loading setup to establish relationships between loaded entities. Links applications to applicants, bookings to applicants, and enquiries to projects.
      Parameters:
      applicants - List of loaded applicants
      officers - List of loaded HDB officers
      managers - List of loaded HDB managers
      projects - List of loaded projects
      applications - List of loaded project applications
      enquiries - List of loaded enquiries
      bookings - List of loaded flat bookings
      receipts - List of loaded receipts

    • saveData

      public static void saveData()
      Saves all system data to persistent storage. Collects data from various controllers and uses file manager to save entities.

    • initializeBookingController

      private static void initializeBookingController(List<FlatBooking> bookings, List<Receipt> receipts)
      Initializes the BookingController with loaded bookings and receipts.
      Parameters:
      bookings - List of flat bookings to set in the controller
      receipts - List of receipts to set in the controller

    • initializeWithdrawalController

      private static void initializeWithdrawalController(List<Withdrawal> withdrawals)
      Initializes the withdrawal controller with a list of withdrawals.
      Parameters:
      withdrawals - The list of withdrawal objects to be set in the withdrawal controller

    • initializeAuthController

      private static void initializeAuthController(List<Applicant> applicants, List<HDBOfficer> officers, List<HDBManager> managers)
      Initializes the AuthController by adding all loaded users.
      Parameters:
      applicants - List of applicants to add to the auth controller
      officers - List of HDB officers to add to the auth controller
      managers - List of HDB managers to add to the auth controller

    • initializeProjectController

      private static void initializeProjectController(List<Project> projects)

      Parameters:
      projects - List of projects to set in the controller

    • initializeReportController

      private static void initializeReportController()
      Initializes the ReportController. Currently, a no-op method as reports are generated on-demand.
